comment: Terrible at lectures, has a bad attitude, and thinks everyone is trying to be a doctor someday and do research. Would go out and drink with her but worst professor ever.

For an online class this was very difficult. She constantly wanted us to read the book and said how their would be test questions from the book. At least 10 questions on each exam was on material I had never even heard of. Studying her lecture notes and the book will not prepare you for the exam.

Had this professor for Elements of Genetics last semester and Evolution this semester. Got a B in Genetics and will get an A in Evolution. Best prof in Kent Biology! She cares and wants you to learn. I just finished the online section of this class and earned an A. If you do the assigned reading and study the materials she puts on blackboard the exams are straightforward. She gave extra credit that was fun.
Class was organized and the prof gave great study materials. Met with her in office hours and she was so helpful. You have to study and pace yourself. I learned a lot about genetics.
Do not take online.

Organization is a big problem with this professor. Her directions were typically unclear and her exams were nothing like any of the information she supplied you with. I was a not a fan of genetics to begin with; now I simply despise the subject.

One of the best professors at Kent, she loves what she teaches and that carries across in her lectures. You need to read the book and attend her lectures. Took Evolution with her. Her course is tough but she supplies you with a lot of study materials. Her questions were application questions so you really have to know the material. She's definitely a good professor and does her very best to help her students succeed with a lot of extra credit.

I took Elements of Genetics with her last fall. She is a great lecturer and made me want to learn more. Now I watch for articles about genetics and I even can mostly understand them. human genetics online exams are really hard there is NO proctoring  so textbook use is available and powerpoints can be used etc we had a pedigree project for us to formulate any inherited traits we may have in family 5 exams which are sooo hard her multiple  choice questions are very difficult and tricky you must pay attention to them closely

Dr Groff gave out many powerpoints lecture materials exam reviews 4online genetics which was really helpful but her exams are the hardest ever two answers may be right but one is more correct and better than the other It takes weeks of studying to get and know and get an A on her type of exams I even met her for her office hours she made available

This was my first online class and genetics is hard for me. This professor provides really good study materials. The pedigree project is fun and the prof sent good feedback. Tests are challenging be prepared to work.

Great teacher not sure who could state otherwise. She's not a pushover and u need to work to get an A. But she's fair and wants u to succeed. If u want to learn genetics and not focus in stats u need to take her. I tell all my friends to take her.

In all honesty, she's not a good teacher at all. She's a very nice person, but the only reason i went to class is because of the clicker quizzes each day. If you just read from the book, read her powerpoints, transcripts, and study guides, you'll be fine. Just go to class, but do some other class' hw since her lectures are not helpful.

TAKE THIS CLASS IN FLORENCE. if you are a bio major and need this for graduation i highly recommend taking this class during the 4 week florence summer semester. yes the classes are long. yes theres a test every week. BUT you are in florence italy! she was so helpful and understood that you wanted weekends to travel and have fun.

Before taking genetics I heard it's a hard boring class. Dr. Groff changed my mind I guess others hadn't taken the course w her. She is  a smart lady, fun, and makes the class fly by. she doesn't have an accent.  If you do not go to class you wont pass because of clickers. Test are hard and application based; there are no definition questions.  She gave 30 points of extra credit, 100pts of hw Final is not cumulative and it is really easy to pass her class. I failed all three tests got a D on the final and got a C+   so take her.

Nice lady, great teacher. Does NOT have an accent despite her name. Attendance is not mandatory but she does give clicker quizzes (sometimes unannounced) often for participation points. Dr. Chiu-Groff makes this subject fascinating. You have to work hard to get an A. She is a fair grader and really tries to help students succeed. She uses good examples and introduces you to the latest science articles. I never thought evol as a modern science but she makes you see this.

Chiu is a challenging professor, but I wouldn't say that she is difficult. She provides lecture transcripts of every ppt which are the way to go for studying for exams. She talks a lot and rambles on especially about her son. There are clicker quizzes but you get full points for just doing them. She also offers an extra credit assignment. She's teaching genetics next semester so I would definitely take it with her.

She is really outgoing. Shes very easy to understand (doesn't even have an accent so don't let her name throw you off). Its clear that she has a deep understanding of her field. easy easy class
