She is so unorganized and messes up everyones grades. I don't understand how she is allowed to teach this class. I only took this class because it was a good time, but don't do it.
Very difficult class and is very hard to understand
Just awful she does not know how to teach

I took her Intuitive Calculus class last semester and it was so unnecessarily difficult. She barely teaches anything, most of the time during class I had to block out everything she said otherwise I would end up more confused. I learned more through the resources in MyLabsPlus. And the class is based around group work, take that as you will...
you learn off youtube so the only reason you go to class is to turn in papers. my little sister could teach it just as well
She is an awful teacher do not take this class, take it online if you can because that is the only way you learn

I took her class online because I'm too busy to dedicate classroom time. Her tests are awful. Derivatives will become your worst enemy. Her lectures are nonexistent. There is no extra credit. She makes so many mistakes that she's lucky the computer grades your homework. Can't believe Kent State takes your money and allows this level of amateurism.

She is literally the worst professor I've ever had. The class structure is based on group work, and they're assigned to you. Group member withdraws? Too bad, have to do it yourself. If there's an option to take a different professor: DO IT. DO NOT TAKE HER. Once asked if there were any questions, watched someone raise their hand, then ignored them.

I would NOT recommend anyone take her class. I had to teach myself the material in order to pass the quizzes & exams even after going to each class. Most students in her class are struggling for a decent grade while other classes are doing fine. Her blackboard grades make no sense either. Final is worth 25% of your grade so choose your prof wisely!

DO NOT TAKE CLASS WITH HER. Her lectures are so confusing that you have to teach yourself all the material. She messes up while doing work on the board and students must correct her all the time. If you ask for help she gets mad at you and makes you feel stupid. If you can switch out of her class do it ASAP.

She's beyond confusing and extremely disorganized. I'm lucky I took stats in high school or I would've never passed. I had to teach myself everything using the book or youtube tutorials. Lots of pointless group work, and she waits until the last 15 minutes of class to give quizzes.

If I knew how bad she was I would have changed classes. Nice, but I had to correct her several times myself and on tests. She admitted she made a mistake but still not give back credit. Not to be disrespectful, but she does not know how to use proper grammar so when she asked for the answer, I had to explain to her and her TA what a preposition was

Lectures always feel long. Little to no help when it comes to class time. So hard to understand that not even the class tutors know what she's talking about or would always have to correct her. Overall, you basically teach yourself EVERYTHING!
Very unorganized as far as grading, homework, and classwork. Would not reccomend.

I  took this class my first semester of my freshman year and I wish someone would've told me to run!! I had to teach myself a majority of the material through the online homework and the book. She assigns alot of confusing group work and she picks who your group partners will be! She miss graded EVERY exam.

You know a class is bad when the student aids are in the corner falling asleep... This class was terrible. She mis-graded our tests every single time and would have to re grade them. She would give us in class examples and then say she did it wrong. I hate math, and she did not help whatsoever. RUN WHILE YOU CAN .

This teacher was one of the worst i have ever had in my life. If you are good at math then you can teach yourself and do fine but she marks wrong answers on quizzes that are right and if you don't catch them you won't get credit. Even on her tests too she will mark the wrong answer as right. You can't understand her and she is so disorganized.
This is the worst class I've ever taken in my life. You cannot understand anything she says. She relies more on group work than actual notes. DROP IT WHILE YOU CAN.

I've never had a prof that made me want to drop out more than this one! her exams always had mistakes. She made even the simple math complex. she asks you to use your calculator in class but never allows it on tests. she kept adding quizzes on top of quizzes & people had to correct her all the time bc she would go to fast and mess her math up.

Cant understand her. Has no idea what she is talking about-has to ask the student helpers. Barely updates blackboard. Every class she gives reading quizzes and every week she also gives quizzes on material. A ton of online homework and group work that she doesn't give you enough time to do. Only good thing is that she exam Q's come from review.

If you can bear her english, you'll do fine if you do the work. An ALEKS class, meaning that the ENTIRETY of the work is done on a computer, solving math problems. The workload for this, and all ALEKS classes, verges on insurmountable if you don't do well on the Day-1 'what-do-you-know-so-far' test. The ONLY teaching is done by you to yourself.

Even though she can be nice, she doesn't know her material as much as I would expect from a professor. She also does not know how to organize a class as most of her homework questions are due at 10 am the day before class when most professors set the time at 11:59 pm. the day its due. Try to avoid her class because she doesn't  explain things well.

she might be hard to understand at times, but god forbid a professor actually makes you study.. shes very sweet and cares about her students. she knows her stuff if you dont, its your job to get extra help which she offers!

This teacher is horrible. She gives examples that are for more advanced math and doesn't understand why students are struggling. Over half the class failed because she wasn't able to help us. She changes how you do things, and even tells you the incorrect way to solve a problem. AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

Seriously, just don't. She's not willing to stop and help if you don't understand the section. She moves very quickly and goes perfectly with the syllabus which is the only good thing. If you care about your GPA, stay away!
Awful teacher.  I don't think she knew the subject matter at all. She was all around an atrocious teacher. Do not take her.

took her online modeling algebra class on Learn. It was so confusing. Two many assignments in too many diff places; hard to keep track if you have other classes to worry about. dates are also all wrong. exams had questions we weren't supposed to study that week. easy if you keep track.

I had her for Algebra 2 and 3. She doesnt talk b/c its all on computers so its nice. She strongly believes that you have to meet certain percentages every week but it doesnt really matter. On test days, you can just go in after class when everyone is gone and gives you more time. Easy class. Nice not having to be lectured.

She is very sweet professor but she is not very clear. However, if you go to talk with her, she will offer a lot of help. She cares about her students. So if you take her and you are not doing good, go talk to her and ask for help. She uses the book a lot! all her notes are taken out of the book.
Even though there is a bit of a language barrier, Professor Pham knows her stuff.  Keep talking to her if there's a problem.  QUESTION HER if she does not clarify assignment requirements!

Well, first of all, there is a bit of a language barrier, as she has an accent, but it's not too bad. She is nice, and she'll usually help you if you ask. There is frequently confusion about something... Once in awhile she messes up example problems. If you show up and take notes, the class isn't bad, but if you don't you can fall behind quickly.
She's really not that bad.  If you go to class you'll do fine, there's nothing on the tests that she doesn't go over in class. I though she was a good teacher.

I took this class during the school year and had no idea what was going on, and failed with a D. I took this class over the summer and it was sooo much better! As long as you attempt your homework every night you get a perfect score! She took thins much slower than the previous teacher, and was so helpful. I passed the second time with an A-!

Seriously the worst class of my college career. Take this course if you want an excuse to fail out of college. She has no idea what she's doing and messes up when grading quizzes. Her tests are on material not even covered in class! Don't sign up for her if you value your GPA!

Always late, grumpy, and giving homework.  She gave homework everyday, and it was very time consuming.  There were also many tests and quizes and group projects.  whenever she did sample problems she would get the wrong answer.  Bad attitude, and bad knowledge.  DON'T TAKE HER CLASS
i did not like her at all. she wasnt a good teacher at all.

She is by far the worst professor ive EVER had. Late everyday, cant speak english, assigns homework without teaching material, unexpected quizzes, lots of homework, needs help from class to complete EXAMPLE problems, wrong answers at times, and she is ALWAYS in a foul mood. DROP NOW!

She is freaking horrible. Seriously study the book as much as possible and just prepare yourself for questions you would not even know to be on the test. Constantly didn't know how to solve problems, late every day to class and blames it on a copier, horrible. I learned absolutely nothing from her.

she sucks, she'll answer your questions but it's almost like she doesn't know them herself.  She moves too fast, she's always late to class, then always runs over time, forgets what she assigned you and what you're supposed to turn in.  It's ridiculous, she's ridiculous.  DROP!

The class is very demanding. IF you miss a class here and there be ready to buckle down and catch up. She moves at a quick pace, and teaches in a backward teaching manner--- assigns homework first then teaches the lecture the next day. She is very detailed, a little crazy and rough around the edges. Ive always struggled with math but I passed!
you cant understand her at all and she does not teach well at all
She is the worst on making things clear and was really bad at explaining things.
I've never gotten a good math grade.  Her constant demand for working hard paid off.  She was a little hard to understand at times, but not that hard.  I thought she was really good overall.

She knows her stuff but has a hard time getting it across due to her bad english! She seems irritated and mean but i think its only bc the students always talked about her and made fun of her :( She trys her best to explain but Im warning you the hw and class work is MUCH easier then the quizzes and final! Get a tutor...
Shes the worst professor at kent, if you have her on your schdule, drop now
I hate this teacher. She is the worst teacher I have ever had.
Hard to understand and not very helpful in studying.
yea...after a month or two of getting 40/100 on her tests i decided to drop the class. other than that shes pretty funny to watch...she uses both hands to write on the board!..its crazy
she teaches too fast and does not spend any time reviewing

She is the worst prof. ever!!! i went to her office hours to get help and she didnt help at all, all she did was sit on the computer and tell me how bad i was failing. If you get this class drop it before its to late!
awful, awful teacher. DROP THIS CLASS IMMEDIENTLY!!!! do not expect to get high grades in this class, can't understand her, and her tests are over stuff covered in the book(not what she teachers)

By far the worst algebra teacher ever! I suggest dropping the class because half of her class drops/fails anyways. She doesn't even try to help the failing students..which is around 40-50 percent of her class...
No Comments

Very hard to understand, ridiculous method of teaching, writes stuff on board and dosn't explain anything...expects students to figure stuff out on their own if they don't understand...not helpful at all...DROP class asap.

worst teacher ever.  she cant even speak english and doesn't teach anything good.  all she does is writes tons of stuff on the board and doesn't stop to explain any of it.  if you get her class, drop it asap

Worst Prof I've had. He pissed off almost his entire class with how bad his instruction was and his poor interactions with students. Even had a complaint lodged against him for it. If you want to understand the material, you will have to attend his office hours. Avoid him for sake of your mental health, but he is survivable, bc of his extra credit
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: Hes really not that bad. Just take notes on what he says during class, and youll be fine. I didnt attended class except on quiz/exam days, and I had 103 percent overall because of how much extra credit. I even slept through some quizzes. Hes nice and is passionate about philosophy. I dont get why people are being so mean towards him.

Would not answer student emails and would be vague with questions during class. Laughed at students who answered incorrectly or asked questions. Maybe it would be different in an in-person environment, but it was not a good online course. You need to do all extra credit opportunities to pass with a decent grade.
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Lecture heavy--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: no textbook but 2 $10 books needed- so dry- doesn't explain assignments well- doesn't create a good environment for discussion- makes you feel stupid for asking questions-shoots questions down- i was really excited for this class and i do all of the assignments/reading however it was still a struggle to get a good grade
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Even with a year of entirely remote classes due to covid, this was by far the worst professor I had during my freshman year at KSU. The man loves to lecture, but does not have the voice, attitude, or pace to lecture effectively. Quizzes and exams are a nightmare, but he will drop your 3 lowest grades there. He also doesn't count attendance.

This class is horrible. Attendance isn't graded, but if you don't go to class you'll fail everything. He's impossible to get ahold of and he will never respond to any email you send him. He rambles all class then gaslights his students when they ask questions because they don't understand things and he won't explain. We're all teaching ourselves.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: You HAVE to attend lectures. Not for a grade, but just to understand what is going on. He also gives extra points for participation but you have to answer the questions correctly in order to get those points. Only issue is, if the answer isnt 100% what HE wants, youre wrong. Hes rude to students who ask questions during class. And he rambles
ratingTags: Lecture heavy--Graded by few things--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Doesn't upload a schedule to blackboard and won't send emails about dates or deadlines so if you don't attend and pay attention to every second of every lecture, you'll miss every quiz and exam and paper because he literally won't respond to emails. That being said, attendance isn't mandatory, so I guess that's a plus. Avoid this dude at all costs.

His lectures are very boring and his voice is also hard to want to listen to. I chose this philosophy class because I thought it was going to be easy, but I ended up dropping it because it was my worse grade. I am in nursing school and I have more important classes to put time forth and not a philosophy class that means nothing to my degree.

Hes actually a very nice and funny professor, hes just very passionate about philosophy so its easy to get lost sometimes. It can be hard to pay attention so I dont recommend taking this course if you arent actually interested in philosophy. Lots of reading and quizzes but you also have the option to utilize extra credit.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: He gives you extra points every now and then and he drops three of your lowest quiz grades, but the questions on his quizzes make no sense at all. They don't really connect a lot with the notes and are really hard to comprehend. He is very nice and is always trying to involve the class. His exams are pretty difficult though.
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Beware of pop quizzes--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Graded through quizzes and exams only. Extra credit is helpful, so do all of it. It will save your grade. It is difficult to pay attention in class due to the boring material and lackluster lectures. Syllabus changed frequently throughout the course and attendance grade was dropped half way through.
ratingTags: Lecture heavy--Test heavy--Graded by few things

comment: I was not a fan of this professor or this class. You read the books outside of class, and then during class you just go over his book notes. The books are challenging to read, and he does not offer much insight. But he gives 8 quizzes, but he drops the lowest 3 scores which is nice. He also gives occasional extra credit which helped my grade.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: He is amazing! He offers lots of extra credit, there are 8 quizzes but he drops your lowest 3, gives good reviews before exams, and discusses the books so much you don't have to read. It an easy course with a really great professor. You can tell he cares a lot and does his best to help you succeed. 10/10 would recommend

Hes a great professor. He gives 8 quizzes then drops the lowest 3. They're always announced ahead of time and he tells you exactly whats on them with a bonus question. Do the 20 pt bonus assignment on the first day and you should be fine. You get extra credit for going to every class. Its super easy if you put in an ounce of effort and want an A
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: I took this class twice - the first time I failed. And the second time I got an A. The difference was I actually went to class regularly the second time. If you go and you do the work, you will pass. He really cares about his students and he's one of the only professors I ever had that had a real talk with me and shaped my educational future. 10/10

Great professor though I wouldn't suggest taking this class if you have trouble with reading comprehension/test-taking. Professor Uher clearly cares about what he teaches and gives a lot of opportunity for bonus points. Only downside is he doesn't post grades online throughout the semester so you need to reach out via email to see where you stand.
ratingTags: EXTRA CREDIT--Lecture heavy--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: DO NOT WASTE MONEY ON THE BOOKS! You don't need it. He tells you all that you need to know in his long boring lectures. The lectures are not very interesting although he does try to through jokes in. Class is out of 300 pts. 100 for the final, 100 from two midterm exams and 100 from your best scores on 5 of the 8 20pt quizzes. Take at your own risk
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT--Tough grader

comment: He is one of the worst professors I've ever had. He does not input grades for the whole semester so you are forced to guess what your final grade will be. There is a lot of reading, and the books are difficult to comprehend. I am normally a straight-A student, and this class is one of the worst I've ever taken. Tests/quizzes are very difficult.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: Clarence Uher made the Intro to Ethics class I was in way harder than it needed to be. I am a very hardworking student with a good work ethic and I still struggled to keep my grade up. His lectures are incredibly dry, and his quizzes/exams make zero sense. I would not recommend him to anyone, since his class is impossible to effectively study for.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: The class was pretty ok. As long as you show up and do the minimum you'll be fine. He drops your 3 lowest quizzes and gives plenty of bonus. Reading the book will help and you get bonus for doing the practices, but it ins't necessarily needed. Overall, I learned a good bit, though the lectures can drag.

Unless you have some what of an interest in the subject of Philosophy I do not recommend this class. He doesn't post any grades at all throughout the semester so I was literally crossing my fingers at the end hoping I did well. The material was confusing, boring and very uninteresting. It's not that hard, but definitely not enjoyable.

The first day of class he offered a twenty extra credit points, he drops 3 of your worst quizzes, and announces all of the quizzes beforehand. This class can be really boring because it's a philosophy course, but you can tell he tries to keep the class engaged. He makes a lot of jokes and tells a lot of stories. He cares about his students a lot

I would not recommend this introduction class to anyone. It's based solely on philosophy, and if you're someone like me that doesn't understand it even when you study, this isn't the class for you. The professor LOVES philosophy and only lectures, which doesn't help you to learn it or pass the class.

Taught the material somewhat well but the class itself was very unorganized. Did not manage time in class well enough. Spent too much time answering questions from homework and quizzes, which did not leave enough time to fully teach the material. Was not always accessible after class.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: This man's voice and lectures are very boring. I never listen to what he says in class. He gives 5 quizzes and drops the lowest 3 and he gives you 3 exams. He gives you the opportunity to go into office hours to correct your quiz. I got a 12 out of 20 on one and I just listened to him talk for 20 minutes in his office and he gave me a 20/20
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: The rest of these reviews seem to be more focused on bad grades rather than Mr. Uher himself. He is an amazing professor and one of the few that genuinely cares about his students' education. He's hilarious and structures the class so that it is difficult to fail. I genuinely wish KSU had more profs like Professor Uher.

He is the most boring teacher I've taken. He cares about the subject but he expects you to understand it like the back of your hand when it's actually really hard to understand. Would never tell anyone to take this class.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Try this class if you need a kent core math credit. He will personally work with you to help understand the material. Very accessible office hours. Take it in the summer, it's quicker and easier. He's boring but I don't expect formal logic to be entertaining. Use the CD, he loans out textbooks in the summer. He tells you exactly what's on the test.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria

comment: Would not recommend his Ethics class to anyone!

A lot of students consider him "boring", but I think it's because of his tone of voice. He just speaks in a dry tone, and you have to be mindful of what he's saying; it's easy to tune out. But if you listen, it's not hard to understand the lectures. Extra credit opportunities. Nice, fair guy. Old-fashioned in terms of phones, etc. Get the book imo.

Professor Uher is by far the most dullest, most boring human being on earth. His lectures are SO long and honestly if you look up at the clock during class, you may cry that only one minute has gone by since you last checked. Gives 8 quizzes, but drops the lowest 3 so that is great. DO the extra credit assignment on the first day, and go to class!

Uher's class was very long and boring, which made it extremely hard to pay attention. All notes are provided online. Two exams are hard so study a lot for those. Multiple tests are also hard, although three lowest scores are dropped. One extra credit provided at the beginning of the year, do it! Pay attention, ask questions, and study!!!

He was very helpful and willing to answer any questions you have as long as you take the time to go to his office hours. His lectures are long, but as long as you understand the main points of the material, you'll be fine for the exams. Quizzes are harder than exams, but he drops the three lowest quiz grades out of eight.

If you're not interested in this field, do not take the class. If you do however enjoy the field, this class is enjoyable. He is a great professor and knows what he's talking about. His lectures are supplemented by witty jokes, and he is always there to help. Quizzes are tough, but you can drop the lowest 3. Probably the nicest professor I've had.

Prof Uher is nice, however he is very disorganized when it comes to what is expected. We do not stick to the syllabus and his class is so boring. Do not take this class unless you want an hour and 15 mins of doing nothing but drooling. He drops the 3 lowest quiz grades and posts notes online which is nice but the material is boring.

If you have insomnia I highly recommend that you take Doctor Uher's Intro to Ethics class. He is without a doubt the most dull professor I've ever had. Attendance is mandatory, miss more than two and your grade drops a letter. Do the extra credit, material can be kinda tough. His notes are unhelpful, 8 quizzes and drops lowest 3. Tends to drone on.

Professor Uher  did a good job teaching Ethics. He makes the topics easy to understand and assists with the difficulty of the text that is read.  Easy class, finished with an A. Can't skip class. Be prepared for seemingly long lectures.

Professor Uher is very knowledgeable of the topics he covers in class. Critical Thinking was a good course and he goes pretty in-depth with every concept. Lectures can seem to endlessly drag on, but the course is very easy if you are good at reasoning through things. Gives extra credit, I had over 100% in the class at the end of the semester.

He doesn't know to teach. Plain and simple. He says um every other second. 331 in one class to be specific. Would never take him again. His grading varies from essay to essay on exams and doesn't know how to explain anything. Good luck if you take him. He blows ass

Insanely boring. Confusing when he lectures, and refuses to use Blackboard so you cannot monitor your grades which is incredibly annoying. The class itself is difficult, but he does not make it any easier. Avoid him and this class at all costs!!!

Boring guy, boring teacher. Attendance is mandatory and if you have more than two unexcused absences he will lower your grade a whole letter. No homework. Offers a lot of extra credit so you'll probably get an A but won't understand anything. If you ask him something he'll talk for an hour repeating himself but not answer your question.

Definitely knows what he is talking about. Unfortunately that's his biggest problem. He literally talks for the entire class period and doesn't offer any other learning opportunities for a very difficult subject. Strict on in class rules (mandatory attendance, no phones or laptops, etc.). I like his grading system & he's nice. You need the books.

A good Professor, simply put he is covering some of the most difficult subject material college students are required to take at Kent and is very drawn out in his lectures. His classes are difficult, but there are helpful SI tutors for his courses. Intro to Ethics is also very book oriented and in the class it can be hard to focus. He makes it easy

Horribly boring and confusing. Sense it is a philosophy class, it requires a clear and concise instructor. He is not. Quizzes and Exams are not difficult to understand, but anything from the whole semester could be on it. He is not organized and ends up repeating himself and stopping to figure out what he is actually talking about. Do not take him.

Very very very boring. Repeats himself a lot. Confusing most of the time. Exams were simple but you have no idea what will be on them. You just have to study everything from the whole semester and hope you will remember something on there. Nice guy, but doesn't know how to teach without making you fall asleep.

He's a nice guy, overall, but fin another prof. for this class. He trips over his words, can get you easily confused if you are just learning this material. Never really teaches, just does problems on the board and expects you to catch up.

If you're good at reading philosophy books, and let's face it you're probably not, then I would not recommend taking this professor. He can't hold the attention of the class and just sort of rambles the information to you.

This is a horrible teacher, philosophy is hard enough he makes it even worse by making all of his test and quizzes the way he thinks of things. Unless you have taken another philosophy class or read and studied the books "Platos Republic", and "The Meditation" This class will be very difficult due to teaching.

Professor Uher is a very monotonous speaker and often trips on words.  His class is very boring.  You should probably read if you take this class. He did ,however, offer 20 points of extra credit and his exams weren't too hard. He also has 8 quizzes and drops the lowest 3
I never really knew what was going on in the class. May have been partly my fault as im not a Philosophy major. The tests were difficult and he was very hard to follow during his lectures.
Great professor. Will take time to help you work things out. Very difficult class, although attendance is not mandatory it is highly recommended.

Sitting through one of Uher's classes is like watching dry toast cool down.  Boring, awkward, and makes potentially interesting material boring and painful.  Only exams and quizzes, in which many of the questions are irrelevant to the course material.  Find a different prof!

The worst class of my life. I am a good student and barely got out with a D+. Tests dont show your knowledge of the topic at all and he doesn't understand how to explain the topic in multiple ways so if you don't understand what he is saying then don't bother asking. I do not recommend taking this class with this prof EVER!

Dr Uher is a good professor. The subject is very hard to teach but he slows it down and makes it comprehensible. He tries to joke around and is more than willing to help if you go to his office hours. Good class. However, you need to buy the book, and its KENT STATE specific so kind of expensive.Also can't miss too many days of class. Extra Credit

THIS CLASS IS SO BORING. He is completely monotone & does not make topics interesting. The books you have to read are ridiculous to understand. I learned more about the books from Cliff's Notes than I ever did attending that class.

This subject is absolutely ridiculous and should not even be taught, and this guy just makes it that much more boring. If he said "house keeping" or "go fishing" one more time I was going to scream. If this class wasn't in the middle of the day I would not have gone unless we had a quiz or test. Be prepared to be REALLY bored!

Had him before for Principles of Thinking. Definitely, not the most exciting guy in the world, but the material is boring, too. He did make things easy to understand, so long as you went to class everyday. Really, he's not hard and it's an easy A. Three tests and multiple quizzes.

Just drop it now! Currently in it,it's hard! Use the CD! Go to class so you know what to teach yourself later! Uher quote of the day: "Ummmmmmm." The book can only be bought @ book store. expensive!!! google "Uher Formal Logic Kent" for syllabus! drops 2 out of 12 quizzes + extra credit. Still hard! But if you must, this is the easiest! class = :'(

Intro to Formal Logic is excrutiatingly boring. Painful even. But this cannot fully be blamed on Mr. Uher when you realize the material can lobotomize even the most lively and charismatic teachers. This instructor does an adequate job of making the subject bearable. He presents simplified notes and does a good job carefully explaining concepts.
Very easy. Drops a lot of quiz scores. Fairly straightforward material. He practically reads out of the book, though, and is easily confused. Nice guy, though.

Intro to Logic was a nightmare because i suck at math, but Clarence made it somewhat tolerable. He's a very nice, quirky man who loves logic even though most people in the class could care less. If you need a math credit to graduate, i would recommend taking Uher. otherwise, avoid!
Sometimes he himself gets confused but for the most part he explains things clear and the sets up the quizzes and exams to a very nice liking.  Just practice the problems at home and you'll be fine.

It's a boring class, but he's not to blame...it's just a boring subject. He's a nice enough guy. If you go to class and keep up with the material, there's really no reason to get less than an A. I skipped half of the classes (like I said, it's BORING!) but still got an A-. If your book comes with the CD, use it! It really helps.

I didn't even know he had dyslexia until I saw the comments on this site.  Principles of Thinking is terribly boring but extremely easy.  Uher isn't a bad teacher.  There are lots of quizzes (pretty easy) and a few exams (also kinda easy).  I had to take the class for my minor.  It wasn't too bad.

the class if tough but its interesting. He is very knowledgeable on the subject and knows how to answer questions completely. He sometimes can be confusing but if you do the homework and keep up with some of the reading then you will be fine.
eh, i just happened to understand logic. other than that, he was very confusing with the was he tried to explain things.

Uher is a great guy, really nice, but kind of awkward.  Formal Logic is math based, so if you aren't good at math you might find this class hard.  Offers tons of extra credit, and is always willing to help out during his office hours.

(intro ethics) very boring class, very boring teacher. if you dont like any form of philosophy dont bother, he is very uptight and needs to relax. always complains about students coming late or leaving early (it was a 7pm class, some ppl have JOBS!!)
Worst formal logic teacher ever!! Hes boring, confusing and makes you feel dumb in class. Take Pendleton for fomal logic if you can! Avoid this man.

This prof suffers from Dyslexia which I found out via the 2nd lecture. He admitted it rather embarrassed when writing a word one the board. He was teaching Formal Logic and could not even articulate a clear and concise thought train. His teaching experience was POOR at best. I had to drop.

If you feel like doing an independent study course than this class is for you!!! (because you don't learn a damnnn thing in the class room)He mumbles, doesn't know his material, his tests and quizzes are tricky because you have to choose the "best" answer not the "right"on because they all are at some level "right"

Professor Uher is a great teacher! I highly recommend taking any courses from him.  Some students say that he is boring, and that he stutters, but they're just ingorant brats who really didn't come to class all that much anyway.  Professor Uher gives great notes, offes help when asked, and, morever, is a really nice man.

BORING... that about sums it up for this guy. While he is a nice guy, he is by far the most boring professor I have had at Kent in 3 years. If you dont have to take Ethics... DONT TAKE IT. The readings are old and very confusing and his notes are a joke. His tests are very hard and his wording is confusing. He will seriously put you to sleep. AVOID
this guy cannot talk. he stutters so much. the good side, the class is easy, his grading scale is nice also. besides he's boring, i wouuld take the class just because it's easy
Strays too much from the subject, he always stutters.  Horrible teacher.  Have to remind him what subject he was teaching before he lost his train of thought.
This was a really hard class for me. He never gave you a straight forward answer. He's pretty boring, but he's a nice guy and is willing to help as much as he can.

class was boring but i would still recommend this class. it was a little overwhelming at first because the concepts are so different.. there are a lot of quizzes but he alwyas tells you when they are going to be and drops the 2 lowest.. i would definitely recommend buying the book and using the cd that comes with it, it makes things really easy

if you go to class yu should be alright. Although if you go to class he says um so many times i saw people counting how many times he said it so its hard to get over that fact. Fell asleep a couple of times but he puts notes online but there vague so you need to go to class

Principles of Thinking is boring.  So is this man. He says "um" and "uh" every 5 seconds. Beware, his lectures will put you to sleep. The material isn't hard, but it builds so you have to go to class to be able to know what's soing on.

BORING! Want to die rather than go to class but if you dont go you wont get a good grade. He gives pop quizes and says "ummmm" at least one hundred times a day. He is funny, but I think it's a hard class because he isnt clear on what he's talking about and sometimes  the class has to correct him

Take this, it's a good class with a good prof. He was hilarious. If you go to class it's not bad at all. If you're not a math person this is a great class and Uher is the person to take it from, he goes a little slower than other profs for this class.

He is a very nice guy but the class is VERY VERY boring. I didnt go to many classes. He puts the notes online for you to print out. He gives a lot of quizzes though-- but drops the lowest 2 or 3 scores. The exams are a little tricky... true/false. matching, fill in the blank, mult choice and an optional essay.
He seems like a very nice guy but his class is very, very boring..
He is a nice, timid guy but his Ethics class was very boring.  It was also pretty difficult for a sophomore level class.
This class is easy, but also easy to fall esleep during. He takes a long time to cover the material and reviews a lot, so he's always behind. Reading the books is not even necessary to do well.
This guy rules. Seriously. He knows what he is talking about, and makes sure that you understand the concepts before he goes on to something else. His understated sense of humor amuses me to no end.
Absolutely HORRIBLE...DO NOT TAKE ETHICS WITH THIS MAN!!!
It might've been just me but Intro to Ethics was so hard. Very boring too. He's really nice but seems really timid. Stumbles over her words a lot.
No Comments
Things are fine until you ask a question, or ask to have something clarified, then he gets all confused.
No Comments
No Comments
Intro to ethics is a very hard class to follow but this teacher made it easier

Never has rubrics or clear grading criteria. Impossible to communicate with even though he lectures on how important communication is. Incoherent lectures. Says he gets too many emails to respond to students. Outdated powerpoints and lecture content. Says you can redo assignments if you listen to feedback, but feedback is "recs" or "expand."
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Group projects--So many papers

comment: Absolutely TERRIBLE. Doesn't respond to emails for weeks, yet admits to reading them. Powerpoints haven't been updated since 2009. Says you don't need the book, but gives long assignments straight from the book with no context. Doesn't keep up on grading, posting assignments, or opening course folders. Grades easy, but you learn nothing. Just BAD!
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Group projects--So many papers

comment: If he was Santa on Christmas everyone would be disappointed because this man has absolutely no gifts. He can't teach well, his power-points aren't even spelled right half the time. Will threaten you with a pop-quiz if you don't participate. If you want to lost for a semester take any of his classes. He's a nice guy though.

She is a very nice lady while you are in lab and lecture. Outside of class however, she never answers any emails about any questions you may have. The lectures are super long and very hard to understand throughout. I have taken many nursing classes to this point and this is the only class I have had complaints about a professor in.

Professor Bixler is an incredibly warm and kind professor! She knows her stuff and goes out of her way to help. I always felt like I could reach out to her. Her lectures can be a bit long. STUDY HARD. They're nursing exams so the time you put in is equivalent the grade you get. They're written like the NCLEX so study with those types of questions.

I got straight As all throughout college until this class. Literally impossible to get an A even if you study ALL of the content she gives you. Super nice in lab but the questions on the exams are literal bs and not fair at all. You need to get through nursing school and have years of experience before getting an A on an exam
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy--Lecture heavy

comment: LOL at this professor. She is no help at all and the class lecture is 100 times harder than it needs to be! Lab and clinical are great experiences!! Lecture is her reading off the slides and then not really answering questions clearly in the live lecture. Hopefully you read this and realize soon in the class that you have teach yourself the math.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Graded by few things--Lecture heavy

comment: I LOVED Bixler as a professor and lab instructor. She was so warm and friendly and I felt as though I could ask her about anything and she wouldn't judge me for not knowing something. I never felt bored or stopped paying attention in class. As long as you really pay attention in class and study moderately, you'll pass.

Everything the other rater said is true. His websites are incomprehensible. His explanations are vague and confusing. And if you don't attend his office hours (held during the business day) he will not help you. I'll never take a class from this guy again.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Test heavy--Tough grader

comment: Had him for advanced C# programming, the content was easy but his site and instructions made everything 10x harder. Firstly, English isn't his first language and all of his terrible confusing instructions are hidden on his own personal website that is a complete mess and shared with other classes. Nobody understood what the hell he was asking for.

Had a 5 week summer inorganic chem class with Dr. Bunge. He replied to emails in 24 hours. I liked the posted videos about group elements in the class. lectures were just readings from the slides and homework through sapling was a pain. overall read the slides, study the homework problems, vocabulary and exam bonus points are your best friend.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Clear grading criteria--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Lectures were monotonous, and homework was difficult but some problems were straight from the book. Exams are clearly outlined and weighted you two best exams higher for you grade. He gives 5-10 bonus points for each exam which helps a ton. Study the vocab, formulas and suggested problems and you'll have no trouble in this class!

Lectures videos were an hour long once a week and he read directly from the slide. Not to mention, he was monotoned and I eventually just read through the 70+ slides by myself. The homework is often much harder than what is taught and will take hours to do. Exams are extremely hard too so make sure to study.

very hard and i basically taught myself. the online lectures were supposed to be mon, tues, thurs, and fri but he posted a one hour lecture per week with nothing else because he was "too busy with his kids". the lectures were very slow and boring with little explanation on each topic. even tho he barely taught, the exams were not open note. wack.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Graded by few things--Test heavy

comment: Don't take this class if you haven't already mastered chemistry. This class was a breeze for me because this is my third year studying chem, except now I'm getting credit. If this is your first chem class, stay as far away as you can because his "teaching" is uploading an hour long lecture video once a week. You will learn nothing.
genuinely the worst professor i have ever had. literally just so bad. dont take him

Awful professor. After the first exam, it was all downhill. Reached out for help and he didn't respond the first time, and then when he finally did, was condescending and not helpful. I did all the homework and studied the material and felt I had a good understanding... only to bomb them. Would not take again, exams don't correspond to material!
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Test heavy--Tough grader

comment: Do you want to actually learn chemistry and have someone teach you the material? Yes? Then stay away from this guy. He uploads one video a week of him reading monotonously off of slides, gives you one homework with questions that don't make sense, and his exams are even worse with one review session the day before the exam. Hope you enjoy 60%s!

have him for chem 1 and he is scheduled to do 4 lectures a week and he refuses to do any of them (said he has young kids to watch), instead uploading 1 voiceover a week to cover the content.  only 1 hw grade a week. lots of students have complained about him but nothing has really changed. don't recommend unless u wanna basically teach yourself :(
Passionate professor with great lectures. Always willing to help you. He makes expectations for exams very clear and the homework is not bad. Has a great personality.

Scott is honestly one of the best science professors I've ever had. I saw some of the bad reviews on here before the course. Looking back, I don't know how someone could give him a low score. He cares about his students and makes sure everyone is on the same page. He is always willing to help students who are struggling & knows the material well!!

I took Inorganic 1 online for the 5 week summer class. After reading other reviews I was super scared to take this class since everyone was saying you need to memorize the periodic table. THIS IS NOT TRUE. There are 4 exams and the final which you have to take using ProctorU, but he allows you to use a periodic table, calculator, and scrap paper!
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Took him for Honors Gen Chem 2. He came into the course expecting us to already know everything beforehand since we're honors students, even having the audacity to say "Well you're honors students so you already know 90% of the material." Who says that? His exams are nothing like the practice material, however he grades fair. Great guy, bad prof.

Took him for honors chemistry II. He expected us to know everything about chemistry before he taught it and went through slides way too fast. A lot of formulas and doesnt explain any of the math problems. Exams are nothing like what he teaches. Im a straight A student and am going to get a C- in this class.

So I wasnt able to find much about the online version of inorganic chem when i was getting ready to enroll. Here it is: DONT DO IT. From what I heard, it was supposed to be easier than the face to face class, but I heavily disagree. The online exams are proctored and a colossal pain, the prof doesn't respond readily and online lectures are awful.
Most of the grade is based on three exams and the final but he gives a lot of extra credit with the homework. Also gives 2% extra credit three times a semester for coming to class randomly.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Super easy class, no assignments beyond the required general FYE criteria. He just excitedly spoke about chemistry for about 20 minutes each class, but we were never tested on it. Then the SI leader spoke for a few minutes and usually ended class early. Would definitely recommend this FYE section to anyone
To be honest, he is nothing but a boring. I don't think he deserves the tenure position in KSU. He is not a good teacher, and also he has no a good personality.
bunge was one of the worst professors ive had. puts no effort into his lectures, just reads over his powerpoint slides from the previous semester. not a fun class.
teaching ability is definitely lacking, but the course isn't too demanding. stay on top of things and use mild caution.

Took inorganic chem with him. Had to be one of the most boring classes ever taken. Reads his power points the entire class and makes you memorize the periodic table. Overall easy class if you read slides carefully.

Wow, never had a class with so much inconsistency. Does not make things easy to understand, and if fact does little to make things easy to comprehend in general. Will test you on minute details that are only on one or two slides out of hundreds.The fact that the periodic table needs to be memorized is moronic, that's why its a TABLE.

Awesome teacher! His study guides are very helpful to prepare for the test. He is funny and nice. Very easy grader. You can tell he wants you to do well. He actually helped me learn better than most professors, he helped me in multiple chemistry classes other than the one he was teaching!
Terrible teacher, he never used the textbook after the first week. Class makes no sense and hes really boring. BUT it was kinda easy, u just need to study the study guide he provides

I'm not sure what to think of him. He wastes a lot of time going through detail in many things that are on the powerpoints but not on the exam. He tries to be funny but usually fails. He's a ginger. On the plus side, his tests are really easy if you study the practice exams and go to class.

Awesome Professor! He's pretty relaxed and goofy, He is really good at giving extra help to who needs it, he recycles old test questions, and uses alot of hw questions on the test, he explains main concepts very well, and there is barely any math. he also gives out study guides. pretty easy class if you come and pay attention.

Not the best at lecturing, but pretty much tells you exactly what's on the tests. If you know his test style there's no reason not to get an A in the class. Also, hes extremely helpful 1 on 1 and alot of his test questions come right out of the book exercises.

YOU DONT EVEN HAVE TO SHOW UP FOR CLASS.  THE LECTURE IS DRY AND BORING.  ALL HE DOES IS READ OFF THE POWERPOINT.  HOWEVER, HE ANSWERS YOUR EMAILS IMMEDIATELY, AND HE HAS A STUDY GUIDE THAT IS BASICALLY IDENTICAL TO THE EXAM.  HE ALSO CURVES IT A LOT. A GOOD CLASS FOR THE GPA BOOST!

This is by far one of the worst professors I've ever had. Not only does he not teach, but he's lazy. All he does is read his powerpoints to the class, verbatim. (I can read myself, thank you.) Once when asked by a student if he could do an example on the board, his reply was, "I don't want to get my hands chalky." Seriously? Then don't teach!

Good ole' Sotty Bunge Bunge, creepin out society with every look he will give you. I felt like he was staring at my soul on the daily. We used to call him SBwrong, he loved that. Oveall hes my dudeski. He definitely reps his city. Im not about to take his class though

i agree with the last rating. he is the worst prof in the chemistry building. No help what so ever. Never seen a prof say "I don't know" so many times. Also very inconsistant, first says he is going to cuve then he does says he is not cuving,,KSU could do themselves a favor and get rid of him!
No Comments

I had Dr. Evey during covid and she was very good in critiquing my papers. Her quizzes were straight from the online textbook and very easy. The midterm and final were more difficult then the rest of the classwork which required a ton of studying. This class was probably the most difficult one I have taken so far at Kent State, but I enjoyed it.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Dr. Evey is very professional and knows her stuff. She makes the class educational and fun. There will be assignments and exams that you need to work hard for, and the text will come into use.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Clear grading criteria

comment: Julie was a really fun teacher to have. Every class was enjoyable. I took her during covid, so we weren't in person, but she knows how to keep an online class engaged. She asked us questions and shared anecdotes as well as let us tell our stories. I looked forward to class everyday. Her tests are hard though. But she did 1 part proctored and 1 not.
Easy class, two 10 ten question quizzes online each week over a reading, and 6 assignments. Shes nice and isnt a tough grader.

Dr. Marks seems like a nice guy who really wants to teach students about Marketing. My biggest gripe with the class is it is taught 100% by course notes. Theyre 300+ pages and you cant use a digital copy on the tests. Questions based on the lecture are more geared toward verifying the student watched the lecture as opposed to checking knowledge.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Dr. Marks is a great professor! Weekly quizzes can be taken up to 5 times, and there is a midterm and final which are challenging, but are open book open note. Lectures are easy to fall behind on, so try to keep up, they aren't hard to sit through. You should buy the lecture notes it helps a lot!

One of the worst professors I have taken in my entire +3 years at college. 50% weekly mini-test (kind of easy), 20% midterm and 30% final. Both the midterm and the final are hard because it is hard to study for such a very large material with a huge test bank! I don't recommend him but I know there is no other choice!
You need to know how to play the game. Prepare for taking tests and mini tests instead of learning the material, and you will get an A

If im being honest I went to the lecture the first day and thats it. I didn't watch one of the online lectures. The quizzes are all on quizlet. Do not buy the lecture notes! Instead rent the textbook to use on the exams. Go to the index to find the subject of the question rather than sorting through the notes. I put MINIMAL effort and got a B+.
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Test heavy--Clear grading criteria

comment: Larrys lectures cover a lot of material and you MUST read the book in accordance with the Mini-Tests. Stay up to date and know where most terms are in the notes/book, and you WILL pass. Midterm/Final is open book and open note, but again, dont get lazy, because all that by itself wont carry you.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: All in person lectures are filmed and greatly edited to Blackboard after each class so if you miss class, all the material is easily accessible. Multiple extra credit options. Very friendly professor and tries to make class entertaining.

I really enjoyed Professor Marks. He really wants you to learn. He is upbeat in his lectures so it makes it easier to pay attention. I took the online version and I would recommend it because for midterm/final you take it on your own time. Highly recommend. His class is easy, did the bare minimum and currently have an A. A lot of extra cred as well

Standard lecture class with weekly homework assignments (which you can retake up to 5 times), and 2 non-comprehensive exams. Some extra credit. The lectures are recorded so you can watch them whenever; exams are open book open note, not too hard with the textbook. Overall pretty average class, Larry is a funny guy too, so I'd recommend it.

I had him Principles of Marketing and he is very lecture heavy. He also comes up to you in the middle of lectures and calls you out for having your phone out or talking. The only grade we have in this class is from quizzes and tests.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Professor Marks gave interesting lectures, and he was knowledgeable on the subject matter. I watched every lecture on 2x speed, so I'm not sure what his real voice sounds like. It is easy to fall behind on the lectures, so try and keep up, or you will regret it later. Overall, he was a pretty cool guy!

Offers extra credit, lectures are interesting and helpful. Gives every opportunity to EARN an A, you just need to put in the work. The other reviewers must have not taken it seriously. Do the work, put in the time and effort, study before all quizzes and test, and you will excel! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!! Dr. Marks is a true Kent State asset.

Great prof. Makes lectures interesting, and I love the online setup. Everything is very clear and it is so easy to succeed if you put in the work. You need to read, and you need to watch and pay attention to the lectures, but it's a great class. 75 minute videos can get annoying, but you can break it up and watch a little every day. Highly rec.

FANTASTIC professor! I wish he taught more business classes at Kent. The course is taught in person recorded and put online so you can be 100% online and drop in to the lectures to listen in. Great professor, great setup, great communication! One of Kent States best professors! Put in the work, and you can thrive! Laziness will yield bad grades!
Awesome Teacher! Makes you work for your grade, but overall a great class. Learned A lot!!!

Lectures are provided online. Uses access code as extra credit, but offers a cheaper option as well.  Online quiz every week, most answers can be looked up. Midterm and final are hard, but open book open note. Passably if you do good on all quizzes and do the extra credit. Book is optional.
Meh

I didn't like him. His lectures are juvenile, almost middle school like. He won't drop a mini test grade. For having 13 100pt tests you think a prof could drop your lowest grade. Nope. His exams are supposedly based off of the review. I took reviews 10x and still saw foreign questions and failed . Im a really good student, I do quite  well usually

Lecture heavy and your grade relies on exams which I failed. There are quizzes too. He is a great speaker, but exams cover a huge test bank. I totally failed this class even though I participated a lot.
ratingTags: TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: the exams are so much of your grade and there is no way to cheat so don't try. even though they are open book the pool of questions are so specific you won't be able to find them even if you study class has too much info. you can get 100% on all quizzes and fail because of the exams. in my class the average score was a 60%!

Interesting guy and fun to listen to, but his tests must have been developed by the devil. Seriously, I did 4 review quizzes (supposedly from test bank) for all chapters to help prepare for exams, most of the questions on the test I'd never seen before or find answers for. Not to mention you get 15 minutes for his 10 question homeworks. Ridiculous

WOW! At first I thought I was going to hate this class but there is only three things you need to pass the class. 1) Buy the lecture notes 2) Buy the book 3) Do the mini-tests. That's all you need to pass the class. You don't even have to study because the exams are OPEN NOTE(lecture notes) AND OPEN BOOK!!!!!

I think for what should be an easy class because Marketing is an easy subject the class is not easy. The mini tests can be a real pain in the butt because there are so many potential questions, it's hard to get a 9/10 or 10/10. He curves tests so that's cool. I took it online which I regret because I stopped watching the lectures after 3 weeks.

Marks is a really funny and interesting professor. He is really passionate about what he teaches. He talks fast, but you have the option of rewatching the lecture on online. His grading criteria is clear and tests are not too difficult. Gives weekly extra credit and weekly quizzes that you use the notes and the book for.
Two exams, I failed both. Huge test bank of questions which makes studying hard.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Class was pretty straightforward. The weekly mini tests are easy if you use quizlet and notes and counts for 50% of your grade. The exams cover a lot of material but the review tests cover the exact exam material so they prepare you for the exam content.

He talks very fast in lectures, often in rambles. His exams cover small points and not the major things which is VERY frustrating because I bombed his exams because of this. You have weekly quizzes, a midterm, and the final so if you don't try, you won't get a very good grade. He needs to restructure his class style, because it isn't working!

I had Dr. Marks for Principles of Marketing. He is hilarious and his lectures are incredibly interesting. He really knows what he's talking about. He sells an outline of his notes for $8 and they are essential to passing the class. All exams are open note and open book, but still difficult. extra credit is optional, but brought me from a B to an A

Principles of Marketing. Dr. Marks is humorous and his lectures are definitely worth going.  All quizes and tests are open book open notes. However, the tests are extremely hard in a way that frustrates you.  I'm an international student and I got 94 in the midterm. I will probably get an A in this class. So you can get an A too my friends. Right?
not a lot to go off of to receive a grade

I took this course online and had a wonderful experience. Marks gives a lively lecture full of relevant examples and information. He's rather quirky and interesting to listen to. There are a lot of opportunities for extra credit, too. Tests are open book/open note (this semester, at least), so it's easy to get an A if you follow his suggestions!

Dr. Marks' knowledge of marketing clearly indicates he is experienced. However, his exams are just unbelievably difficult. Rather than hitting the major points of marketing, he asks specific tedious questions that are unimportant to fundamental principles/ideas. I am a marketing intern for a major company and have a 3.9. Couldn't get above a B-

Took in class section and opted to just watch the lectures online- do not be me and just go to class. Offers extra credit surveys and also if you have the book w/the access code that'll get you some extra credit as well. Weekly quiz/midterm/ and final are all open book and open note so buy book.

Marks explicitly communicates what is expected of you. 5 attempts on each weekly quiz (50% of grade); if you don't get a 100 on these, college may not be for you. The 2 exams come from the exact question pool as quizzes. Book is necessary for quiz/exams, but I never read it, only used as reference. Go to class, do your assignments, get an A.

Buy the textbook, you'll need it. All exams (midterm, final, and 12 weekly quizzes) are open book and open notes. Exams are tough. There is extra credit, that helps a lot. The notes are really long and he talks fast. So get or print out the notes outline, its a life saver.

He his an awful professor who never takes the time to see how his students are doing. In class he laughed at the fact that students were getting 10% on quizzes but never went back over the material. Exam questions are randomly picked and different for each student. Most questions have nothing to do with the topic. They are incredibly specific.

Dr. Marks is a FANTASTIC PROFESSOR! I am a Managerial Marketing major and this is the first marketing class I have ever taken. This professor makes me really enjoy earning my degree. If he taught every marketing class at Kent State, I would gladly take each class. There is a decent amount of course work, but no reason to not get an A.

Conventional wisdom would be for me to say to Avoid. But odds are you cant, if you have to take this course. I had 109 credit hours under my belt and a 3.91 gpa prior to this class, and received my first "C" ever, in his course. I studied studied but his exam questions are impossible. No matter how much you study, you can still do abysmal.

Where do I begin? Final exam average was 66 percent, and he is too oblivious to figure out maybe there's a problem with the style of questions he asks. A professor should test to discern if the student grasped the concept, not find the most trivial things that have nothing to do with anything to ask. You can study hard and still do bad on the exams
His questions are too specific. A lot of the time they have nothing to do with marketing. However, there really is no reason you cannot get a B in the class as long as you do the work.

Pros: Lecture outline is available for purchase $7 for each outline (there are two). Online lecture allows you to watch whenever. Multiple quiz attempts. Cons:  I feel this class should be split up into three exams instead of two. So much material is covered that you become burned out super quickly. Tips: Practice the practice mini tests a lot!

Dr. Marks talks and talks and talks. He moves quickly through lectures but he does post them online after the class. His exams and quizzes require you to basically regurgitate anything that was on the slides or in the book, rather than seeing if you understand marketing concepts.

Make sure you go to class and take the quiz every week. Do well on the quizzes! I would recommend taking the class online so you don't have to deal with him in person. He's extremely rude and pompous. Lame jokes and talks down to students.

He likes his subject, (and his Kumquat flavored Ding-Dongs), and he thinks you must be able to regurgitate every example he ever mentions on his weekly "Mini tests" (quizzes). He also sends about 7+ emails per week, all of which are as long as a normal blog entry.  He also  has open bookopen note assignments, but the answers do not always match.

One of the best online classes I've ever taken! Entire lectures are posted online the same day.  A lot of extra credit opportunities. Great lecture outline with fill in the blanks for notes. There are weekly 10 question mini-tests, which are easy as long as you have the book and take notes, and they can be taken up to 10 times to improve score.

Dr. Marks talks constantly. He interrupts every presentation and person speaking. He will not answer questions. He talks about what he wants to talk about. Dr. Marks is knowledgable but grades everything very hard. Do all homework to your best ability and turn in all assignments on time. He does not allow any absences without an excuse.

To preface, I am usually an A or B student that had a 3.5 GPA. Marks asks overly specific questions on assignments, and tests. Lectures overwhelm with material, so it's hard to know what to study. Fact is, that every single word uttered, or word written in book with be on the tests. I am very upset with this class.
Good professor, easy to understand. Notes were very helpful! Would recommend!

He is an extremely interactive online professor! Posts lectures immediately. Responds to emails ASAP even though he has 800 students at a time! The class was not a breeze, but with enough effort anyone could get an A. Open book/note mini-tests, and real tests. Sometimes his questions were too tedious and not important to overall ideas.

Dr. Marks utilizes the web very well. Posts all lectures and lecture notes and is very clear in his instruction and what is expected of you. If you do your end and learn, he is a great teacher-interesting, clear, and fair. I suspect that if all you want is an easy course, you wouldn't like him.

Tough but fair. Students are given all the tools to succeed and are held accountable for all assignments. Extra credit opportunities and multiple tries on mini-tests give you a chance to bring up your grade if you are struggling. I took online, and it was easy to stay motivated to watch the lectures because he is so energetic in class.

I had Marks for Principles of Marketing online and I loved the way he structured the class. You just watch the lectures online while filling in blanks in the notes he creates for you. Then you take a quiz every week that you should do fine on if you use the book and the notes. His exams are open-book, open-note. He definitely knows marketing.

Very helpful, great guy, knows a lot, and a great teacher. He provides the notes you just have to follow along and add things along the way. The exams are tough, but they are open book and note. Highly recommend him for any class.
FYE class was so easy and we would oftentimes get out early. I love this profs personality and you can he is so friendly and understanding! Take him for FYE
Don't think, just take his class. Enough said.

This class is not very hard if you actually follow the lectures and read the chapters.  There are 13 mini tests which can be taken up to 10 times each, and a final which is 50% of your grade.  As long as you actually follow along in the class, it's really not that hard.  You can use the book on all tests, but reading will make it a lot smoother.

AMAZING. I hate marketing and was so interested and learned SO much. Took class online and its better than any class I actually sat in.  Mini tests weekly but you can take up to 10 times so is not hard to get a good score. Makes everything EASY to understand. Buy notes, you need them and they're cheap!

Dr. Marks posts every his lecture online so you do not need go to class. But the final exam covers 20 chapters from the book and his lecture notes. It's really hard to review...Plus, you need to take mini-tests every week..Difficult class...

He doesn't get to the major points of marketing. He loves to ask specific questions that you couldn't possibly know without the notes in front of you (100+ pages worth) The final was bull. It's comprehensive, random questions, & TOO SPECIFIC. I received a 58%. I'm an A/B student consistently and i'm terrified to see my final grade in the course!

AWESOME TEACHER!! Attendance in class is not always necessary because he posts videos of every lecture online! If I could take like all of my classes with this guy, I totally would! So long as you are not lazy and keep up with the material and you will do fine.

Took online.  Very straightforward.  Quiz every week of 10 questions.  Multiple attempts allowed.  4 questions from lecture/notes.  6 questions from book.  50% comprehensive final.  Interesting lectures.  Due dates are each week.

I took intro to mktg 25010 online. I used book more than notes for studying but you need both. Use book for quiz questions, his notes are phrased differently. You get 10 attempts for quiz and last score is taken. You could only do extra credit if you purchased new book! Final is too hard bec its randomly pooled from all quiz questions. I got a B-

One of my favorite professors. His lectures are entertaining. Mini quizzes every week. All quizzes and exams are open note/open book, but timed. you get 10 tries to take quizzes, but he takes last grade, not best.  DEFINITELY BUY THE NOTES or print them-you won't regret it!!! and you actually need the book. Tons of EC. Take with Marks he's awesome!

Entertaining guy. Talks fast though. You get 10 tries on every quiz and lots of extra credit opportunities. The final is open book open note but is cumulative and timed so you don't have time to look up every answer. Good teacher overall.

I felt that I did not learn as much as I should have.  He is more worried about asking very specific picky questions on the mini tests and final.  I found the final to unnecessarily difficult.  I did receive a 98% before the  curve, but I also did all the extra credit.  Also, he rushes through lecture which makes it difficult to understand.
Probably one of my favorite college professors because he knows how to keep class lively and interesting.

Took online course and breezed right through it. Just buy the book and do the extra credit. Weekly mini quizzes with 10 questions; you can take these up to 10 times! The other half of your grade is the final. All work on Vista except extra credit!

Took course online over the summer. Video lectures were extremely easy to view, mini-tests were not hard at all. Professor very responsive via e-mail. PRINT OUT COURSE NOTES. They will help SO MUCH and help you to write so much less while still learning information and making a study guide for final exam.

Knows a lot about the subject. Mini tests are easy. I got 100's on all of them and the most i too one was like 5 times to get 100. Final is 50% of grade, and it tough. Uses ?'s from the mini tests, and his ? bank is like 2 or 3 thousand questions so there is really no way to study for it.  Open notes / book though.
Great professor. All lectures are powerpoints that can be viewed online. Don't even have to go to class even if you're not in the online section. All tests/final open book and open notes.
Its a good marketing class to take. Open book and notes for all quizzes and final.

Great teacher. Did not have to go to class and posted lectures online to view. 50% mini tests (get 100% on all of them and the class is easy) and 50% final. Really enjoys teaching and makes class enjoyable. Do the work and you will get an A.

Printing lecture notes is a must. The notes are confusing, and long I spent an additional $50.00 printing the notes. No Midterms, however a 'mini test' each week. The tests had multiple errors. Some questions are very specific such as "what did Ron say about this during class?' The final is comprehensive 50% of grade, ridiculous.

Marks' Consumer Behavior class is harder than most marketing classes, and you need to put in the effort. Reading the book is a must, and if you don't normally read the textbook you're going to get half the test wrong. His tests are based on half textbook and half lecture. 3 group projects as well, which are very involved, but not too difficult.

If you'd rather be lazy, not take notes, and study the bare minimum, you will not do well.  If you actually care to learn and understand Consumer Behavior, then Dr. Marks is a phenomenal teacher. You get what you put in. Those who are not willing to earn a high grade, should drop. Those who actually enjoy learning-- I highly recommend.
Hard!!! Pay attention, go to class, Study weeks before the exams and follow his directions very closely for projects!!
What a waste of time... you have to bury your face in the textbook, notes, and attend class EVERYDAY!! this is NO easy A and doesnt take any criticism into consideration.

Professor Bock is not understanding. He does not explain any projects thoroughly nor gives you direction in how to complete the project. Rarely ever gave positive feedback and isn't there to teach you just there to critique your work. For an entry level class he made you feel incompetent. I would not recommend him to anyone.

Beau Bock is not very clear when it comes to projects assigned in this class. If you have the chance to pick your professor for this class, do not pick him. He is very hard to understand when it comes to completing the projects. He went a very contradicting and rarely gives any positive feedback. He leaves everything up to you & you are left alone.

As a freshman at Kenyon in 1984, I took Mr. Lentz's literature class. Simply the best professor I have ever had.  His 50 minute lectures are phenomenal and his knowledge of the subject matter is both encyclopedic and still growing.  He insists on 2 things-punctuality and familiarity with the assignment.  If you cannot do the reading and show up on time do not take his class.  If you can, then do.

He is a wonderful professor. I took his american lit class. It is challenging and some of the books we read weren't my favorite, but he is great! He is one of the kindest people I have ever met. It is annoying that his office hours are really early in the morning, but you should go anyway.
No! Just No!!!! Thanks God he's retiring. His new book is a catastrophe on paperback, too. People should realize that big words don't make a good teacher.

extremely tyrannical in his teaching style and seems to like prostelitizing more than discussing topics from the readings. all i learned from his course was about the kenyon college plagarism conduct
